OL,6,FRainey's barrister said that as he and
OL,7,Fthe co-accused were friends, there was
OL,8,Fno evidence to suggest mobile phone
OL,9,Fcontact with them or his DNA present
OL,10,Fin a car was unusual.
OL,12,FHis barrister also argued that as
OL,13,FRainey was a 'frequent traveller', his
OL,14,Ftrip to Thailand was unrelated to the
OL,15,Fmurder.
OL,17,FThe Crown's case against Ervine also
OL,18,Fincluded his mobile phone usage on the
OL,19,Fevening of the murder in January 2019.
