OL,6,FRegarding Spiers, his mobile phone
OL,7,Factivity with co-accused also formed
OL,8,Fpart of the Crown's case against.
OL,10,FAlleging Spiers was 'male five' in the
OL,11,Fgroup who entered Cluan Place, it's
OL,12,Fthe Crown's case that he had a knife
OL,13,Fin his pocket.
OL,15,FA large 'Ernesto' knife was later
OL,16,Frecovered from the Connswater River in
OL,17,FFebruary 2019 and when Spiers home was
OL,18,Fsearched, an 'Ernesto' knife set was
OL,19,Flocated with one of the knives missing.
