OL,6,FAfter considering the applications for
OL,7,Fall three defendants, Mr Justice
OL,8,FMcFarland acknowledged that whilst
OL,9,Fthere were "flaws and gaps" in the
OL,10,FCrown's case, he was taking into
OL,11,Faccount all the strands of evidence -
OL,12,Fand he refused the defence
OL,13,Fapplications.
OL,15,FFollowing this, barristers for all
OL,16,Fthree defendants confirmed their
OL,17,Fclients would not be giving evidence
OL,18,Fwith Mr Justice McFarland saying "that
OL,19,Fconcludes all the evidence in this
OL,20,Fcase".
